The paper discusses random features, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of large-scale kernel approximation. The focus on leverage scores and their empirical implementation suggests a connection to numerical linear algebra and optimization, which are covered in cs.NA and cs.DS. The experiments mentioned in the paper involve image classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of random features and kernel approximation is also relevant to topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the emphasis on supervised learning and performance bounds, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning).
